{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FYzgjZ4fSqbbMaaEynqwLK","type":"tool_result","content":"A 3-node MongoDB replica set is not deployed in the mongodb namespace.\n\nTask:\n- Deploy a 3-member replica set with authentication enabled. Back it with a\n  StatefulSet named `mongodb-replica` (pods `mongodb-replica-0..2`).\n- Name the replica set itself `mongodb-replica` (the mongod `replSetName` /\n  `rs.initiate` `_id` must be exactly `mongodb-replica`, not the `rs0` default).\n- Create a headless Service named `mongodb-replica-svc` (clusterIP: None) that\n  governs the StatefulSet, so each member is reachable at its stable DNS name\n  `mongodb-replica-<n>.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local`.\n- Create an admin user and an application user.\n- Ensure the replica set is healthy (PRIMARY + SECONDARY members).\n- Confirm data can be written and read from the application database.\n\nCredentials:\n- Admin user: admin-user / admin123password\n- App user: app-user / app123password\n- Store the passwords in Secrets:\n  * admin-user-password (key: password)\n  * app-user-password (key: password)\n\nNotes:\n- Use a keyfile for internal replica set authentication.\n- No operators or CRDs.===PRECOND===\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':probe] $ /bin/sh -c 'exit 1'\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ /bin/sh -c '\nkubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n'\n\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':apply] $ kubectl create namespace mongodb\nnamespace/mongodb created\n\n[precondition:mongo_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'mongo_env_ready':verify] $ kubectl get namespace mongodb -o name\nnamespace/mongodb\n\n===NS===\nNo resources found in mongodb namespace.\n===secrets===\nNo resources found in mongodb namespace.","is_error":false}]},"parent